<i>that Padilla was not
the terrorist mastermind</i>

1340
01:01:01,584 --> 01:01:03,417
<i>the CIA imagined him to be.</i>

1341
01:01:03,500 --> 01:01:06,250
Soufan:<i> They wanted to go</i>
<i>to the United States,</i>

1342
01:01:06,334 --> 01:01:08,000
<i>hijack a uranium truck,</i>

1343
01:01:08,083 --> 01:01:11,125
<i>steal the uranium,
and build a dirty bomb.</i>

1344
01:01:11,209 --> 01:01:13,918
And Abu Zubaydah said, "So how
do you enrich the uranium?"

1345
01:01:14,000 --> 01:01:16,375
And literally, they told him,
"We put it in a bucket

1346
01:01:16,459 --> 01:01:18,542
"and we turn
the bucket very fast,

1347
01:01:18,626 --> 01:01:20,500
and then that's how
it will be enriched."

1348
01:01:20,584 --> 01:01:23,375
And he was just like,
"Yeah, that does not work."

1349
01:01:23,459 --> 01:01:25,292
Zubaydah was like,
"Yeah, yeah, yeah,

1350
01:01:25,375 --> 01:01:26,918
that's exactly
what we should do."

1351
01:01:27,000 --> 01:01:28,000
But he was placating them.

1352
01:01:28,083 --> 01:01:30,125
I don't need this guy
to make a bomb.

1353
01:01:30,209 --> 01:01:33,000
I need this guy because
he has an American passport.

1354
01:01:33,083 --> 01:01:35,209
<i>He knew the value
that it could have</i>

1355
01:01:35,292 --> 01:01:38,417
<i>to people that were actually
planning real operations.</i>

1356
01:01:39,542 --> 01:01:42,209
Soufan:<i> He called KSM</i>
<i>and he told him,</i>

1357
01:01:42,292 --> 01:01:45,584
<i>"I'm sending you these two
operatives, see what they have.</i>

1358
01:01:45,667 --> 01:01:48,542
If you can use them in
an operation, they are yours."

1359
01:01:48,626 --> 01:01:51,834
Gibney:
<i>KSM did send Jose Padilla</i>
<i>to the United States</i>

1360
01:01:51,918 --> 01:01:55,667
<i>allegedly to blow up a series
of apartment buildings.</i>

1361
01:01:55,751 --> 01:01:58,125
<i>He was arrested
in Chicago on May 8th,</i>

1362
01:01:58,209 --> 01:02:01,209
<i>just 15 days after
Abu Zubaydah identified him.</i>

1363
01:02:05,000 --> 01:02:07,250
<i>Despite Abu Zubaydah's
cooperation,</i>

1364
01:02:07,334 --> 01:02:08,834
<i>the CIA and Mitchell</i>

1365
01:02:08,918 --> 01:02:12,042
<i>kept pushing
to turn up the heat.</i>

1366
01:02:12,125 --> 01:02:15,209
Soufan:<i> Even when we</i>
<i>were allowed back in</i>
<i>under our condition,</i>

1367
01:02:15,292 --> 01:02:16,709
<i>they still
were playing games.</i>

1368
01:02:16,792 --> 01:02:20,959
<i>One day I walked in and
I saw a big coffin in the room.</i>

1369
01:02:21,042 --> 01:02:22,417
<i>I actually went in it.</i>

1370
01:02:22,500 --> 01:02:24,500
I'm telling you,
it's not a good feeling.

1371
01:02:26,292 --> 01:02:27,542
<i>You try to be professional.</i>

1372
01:02:27,626 --> 01:02:30,334
<i>You try to focus
on the mission.</i>

1373
01:02:30,417 --> 01:02:33,417
<i>But unfortunately, you know,
every day you bring him back,</i>

1374
01:02:33,500 --> 01:02:36,000
<i>and then they try
to play that game again.</i>

1375
01:02:37,584 --> 01:02:40,125
<i>And at this point,
everything that I was seeing</i>

1376
01:02:40,209 --> 01:02:43,042
<i>was kind of like
borderline torture.</i>

1377
01:02:43,125 --> 01:02:45,459
<i>But now we're even
crossing that line.</i>

1378
01:02:48,042 --> 01:02:50,751
<i>So I called
FBI headquarters.</i>

1379
01:02:50,834 --> 01:02:53,125
<i>I asked to speak
with my boss in New York.</i>

1380
01:02:53,209 --> 01:02:55,000
I said, "Please,
I-I need to leave.

1381
01:02:55,083 --> 01:02:56,250
"I-I cannot stay here.

1382
01:02:56,334 --> 01:02:58,459
"If I stay here, I...

1383
01:02:58,542 --> 01:03:00,584
"I will probably
arrest that guy.

1384
01:03:00,667 --> 01:03:02,876
I mean, this is crazy."

1385
01:03:02,959 --> 01:03:06,751
<i>So he said, "Okay,
I need you to leave
the location immediately."</i>

1386
01:03:08,375 --> 01:03:12,167
<i>And that was the end
of my involvement
in the black site.</i>

1387
01:03:14,042 --> 01:03:16,542
Gibney:<i> Soufan and</i>
<i>the CIA polygrapher returned</i>

1388
01:03:16,626 --> 01:03:18,292
<i>to the United States.</i>

1389
01:03:18,375 --> 01:03:21,125
<i>Mysteriously, the entire
interrogation team</i>

1390
01:03:21,209 --> 01:03:22,500
<i>soon followed.</i>

1391
01:03:22,584 --> 01:03:24,959
<i>All the questions
and answers stopped.</i>

1392
01:03:25,042 --> 01:03:27,209
<i>Abu Zubaydah was left alone
in his cell</i>

1393
01:03:27,292 --> 01:03:31,083
<i>where the only sound
was the hiss of
a white noise machine.</i>

1394
01:03:34,500 --> 01:03:37,292
<i>These are more than 100 pages
of interrogation notes</i>

1395
01:03:37,375 --> 01:03:38,667
<i>from Ali Soufan.</i>

1396
01:03:38,751 --> 01:03:41,584
<i>Though heavily redacted,
we can see they contain details</i>

1397
01:03:41,667 --> 01:03:44,209
<i>about future plots
and portraits of the people</i>

1398
01:03:44,292 --> 01:03:47,000
<i>in and around Al-Qaeda,
how they worked,</i>

1399
01:03:47,083 --> 01:03:48,542
<i>and what they were planning.</i>

1400
01:03:48,626 --> 01:03:50,375
<i>To the FBI,
it was a treasure trove</i>

1401
01:03:50,459 --> 01:03:51,542
<i>of evidence and proof</i>

1402
01:03:51,626 --> 01:03:53,500
<i>that Abu Zubaydah
was cooperating.</i>

1403
01:03:53,584 --> 01:03:55,375
<i>The CIA saw it differently.</i>

1404
01:03:55,459 --> 01:03:56,959
<i>Analysts in Washington
were certain</i>

1405
01:03:57,042 --> 01:03:59,876
<i>he was holding back
because he wasn't telling them</i>

1406
01:03:59,959 --> 01:04:01,375
<i>what they wanted to hear.</i>

1407
01:04:01,459 --> 01:04:03,626
<i>It was time to take
the gloves off.</i>

1408
01:04:05,042 --> 01:04:07,167
Wilkerson:
<i>We've tortured before.</i>

1409
01:04:07,250 --> 01:04:09,834
<i>We tortured
in the Philippines.</i>

1410
01:04:09,918 --> 01:04:11,584
<i>We tortured in Vietnam.</i>

1411
01:04:13,709 --> 01:04:16,334
<i>We are one of
the most violent people</i>

1412
01:04:16,417 --> 01:04:18,083
<i>on the face of the Earth.</i>

1413
01:04:19,667 --> 01:04:24,250
To deny that is
to deny reality.

1414
01:04:24,334 --> 01:04:27,834
<i>But we were the leaders
of the effort</i>

1415
01:04:27,918 --> 01:04:30,042
<i>to push through
the United Nations</i>

1416
01:04:30,125 --> 01:04:31,876
<i>the Convention against Torture</i>

1417
01:04:31,959 --> 01:04:34,042
<i>and Cruel
and Unusual Punishment.</i>

1418
01:04:34,125 --> 01:04:36,209
<i>We were the leaders</i>

1419
01:04:36,292 --> 01:04:38,584
<i>in getting
that phrase in there</i>

1420
01:04:38,667 --> 01:04:40,250
<i>that essentially says,</i>

1421
01:04:40,334 --> 01:04:43,959
<i>"No in extremis
national security conditions</i>

1422
01:04:44,042 --> 01:04:46,834
<i>warrant going beyond this."</i>

1423
01:04:46,918 --> 01:04:49,834
<i>After 9/11, we obviated
the whole thing.</i>

1424
01:04:49,918 --> 01:04:52,834
<i>We said, because of
national security concerns,</i>

1425
01:04:52,918 --> 01:04:54,375
<i>that's out the window.</i>

1426
01:04:54,459 --> 01:04:58,292
This was the first time
that torture as a policy

1427
01:04:58,375 --> 01:04:59,500
was authorized

1428
01:04:59,584 --> 01:05:02,000
by the highest power
in the land.

1429
01:05:02,083 --> 01:05:04,250
Gibney:<i> President Bush</i>
<i>paved the way for torture</i>

1430
01:05:04,334 --> 01:05:07,083
<i>when he signed an order saying
that the Geneva Conventions</i>

1431
01:05:07,167 --> 01:05:08,918
<i>did not apply
to Al-Qaeda.</i>

1432
01:05:09,000 --> 01:05:11,834
<i>That allowed George Tenet
to try something different</i>

1433
01:05:11,918 --> 01:05:14,334
<i>so long as Abu Zubaydah
was believed</i>

1434
01:05:14,417 --> 01:05:16,292
<i>to be a member
of Al-Qaeda.</i>

1435
01:05:16,375 --> 01:05:18,792
<i>President Bush today
has decided that Al-Qaeda</i>

1436
01:05:18,876 --> 01:05:20,584
<i>is an international
terrorist group</i>

1437
01:05:20,667 --> 01:05:22,000
<i>under the treaty.</i>

1438
01:05:22,083 --> 01:05:24,125
Gibney:<i> If members</i>
<i>of Al-Qaeda were different</i>

1439
01:05:24,209 --> 01:05:25,667
<i>from other prisoners of war,</i>

1440
01:05:25,751 --> 01:05:28,083
<i>then perhaps different
interrogation techniques</i>

1441
01:05:28,167 --> 01:05:29,375
<i>could be used,</i>

1442
01:05:29,459 --> 01:05:32,209
<i>but not so different as
to cause permanent damage,</i>

1443
01:05:32,292 --> 01:05:34,834
<i>which could be
evidence of torture.</i>

1444
01:05:34,918 --> 01:05:37,334
<i>That led the CIA
to retrofit a program</i>

1445
01:05:37,417 --> 01:05:39,083
<i>developed after
the Korean War,</i>

1446
01:05:39,167 --> 01:05:41,292
<i>in which we brutalized
our own soldiers</i>

1447
01:05:41,375 --> 01:05:44,834
<i>to prepare them to resist
the brutality of others.</i>

1448
01:05:44,918 --> 01:05:48,918
<i>If we did it to ourselves,
how bad could it be?</i>

1449
01:05:49,000 --> 01:05:52,125
Col. Steven Kleinman:
<i>When I started, I was</i>
<i>a human intelligence officer,</i>

1450
01:05:52,209 --> 01:05:53,584
<i>but then I had
an opportunity</i>

1451
01:05:53,667 --> 01:05:55,209
<i>to go on the other side
of the table</i>

1452
01:05:55,292 --> 01:05:57,083
<i>and work
in resistance training.</i>

1453
01:05:57,167 --> 01:05:59,709
<i>The CIA Enhanced
Interrogation Program</i>

1454
01:05:59,792 --> 01:06:01,959
is the product
of the government's fear

1455
01:06:02,042 --> 01:06:04,209
of what they saw happen
during the Korean War.

1456
01:06:04,292 --> 01:06:05,667
Especially
the Chinese interrogators

1457
01:06:05,751 --> 01:06:07,834
were masterful
in their ability to manipulate.

1458
01:06:07,918 --> 01:06:10,167
<i>They knew how to get people
to say things</i>

1459
01:06:10,250 --> 01:06:12,417
<i>that they didn't want to say,
and the CIA would say,</i>

1460
01:06:12,500 --> 01:06:16,042
"Wow, if they can do that,
what else can they do?"

1461
01:06:16,125 --> 01:06:19,959
Allow me to introduce
our American visitors.

1462
01:06:20,042 --> 01:06:21,209
I must ask you to forgive

1463
01:06:21,292 --> 01:06:23,459
their somewhat
lackadaisical manners,

1464
01:06:23,542 --> 01:06:26,459
but I have conditioned them
or "brainwashed" them,

1465
01:06:26,542 --> 01:06:29,250
which I understand is
the new American word.

1466
01:06:29,334 --> 01:06:30,959
Take this scarf.

1467
01:06:34,042 --> 01:06:36,000
And strangle Ed Mavole.

1468
01:06:40,417 --> 01:06:42,250
-Hey, Sarge. Cut it out. What--
-Tut-tut-tut-tut.

1469
01:06:42,334 --> 01:06:44,083
Quiet, Ed, please.

1470
01:06:44,167 --> 01:06:46,000
Now you just
sit there quietly

1471
01:06:46,083 --> 01:06:47,751
and cooperate.

1472
01:06:48,500 --> 01:06:49,751
Yes, ma'am.

1473
01:06:52,167 --> 01:06:54,459
(choking)

1474
01:06:56,250 --> 01:06:58,542
Gibney:
<i>The popular fear</i>
<i>of brainwashing,</i>

1475
01:06:58,626 --> 01:07:01,209
<i>making prisoners do
or say anything,</i>

1476
01:07:01,292 --> 01:07:02,876
<i>led every branch
of the military</i>

1477
01:07:02,959 --> 01:07:04,918
<i>to create schools
for soldiers</i>

1478
01:07:05,000 --> 01:07:06,250
<i>to learn how to survive,</i>

1479
01:07:06,334 --> 01:07:08,709
<i>evade capture,
resist interrogation</i>

1480
01:07:08,792 --> 01:07:11,334
<i>and, if possible, escape.</i>

1481
01:07:11,417 --> 01:07:13,834
<i>The so-called SERE School
for the Air Force</i>

1482
01:07:13,918 --> 01:07:15,209
<i>near Spokane, Washington,</i>

1483
01:07:15,292 --> 01:07:18,417
<i>is where James Mitchell
taught resistance.</i>

1484
01:07:18,500 --> 01:07:21,209
Mitchell:<i> The basic course</i>
<i>is several weeks long,</i>

1485
01:07:21,292 --> 01:07:22,918
<i>and there's two parts.</i>

1486
01:07:23,000 --> 01:07:25,167
<i>There's the bugs
and berries part of it</i>

1487
01:07:25,250 --> 01:07:28,500
where, you know, they teach you
how to survive and evade.

1488
01:07:28,584 --> 01:07:30,918
<i>And then there's
the second part of it,</i>

1489
01:07:31,000 --> 01:07:33,876
which is the resistance
to interrogation lab.

1490
01:07:33,959 --> 01:07:36,167
And in that,
they essentially have

1491
01:07:36,250 --> 01:07:38,667
what I would call
an undergraduate course

1492
01:07:38,751 --> 01:07:41,292
<i>for protecting secrets.</i>

1493
01:07:41,375 --> 01:07:43,083
<i>Our emotions
can marshal resources</i>

1494
01:07:43,167 --> 01:07:44,959
that we never knew
that we had available.

1495
01:07:45,042 --> 01:07:46,584
But those
very same emotions,

1496
01:07:46,667 --> 01:07:48,918
either fear or anger
or anxiety,

1497
01:07:49,000 --> 01:07:51,292
<i>can also cripple us
in survival situations.</i>

1498
01:07:51,375 --> 01:07:53,792
Eyes on the ground!

1499
01:07:53,876 --> 01:07:56,417
Mitchell:
<i>They expose you to a variety</i>

1500
01:07:56,500 --> 01:07:58,584
<i>of interrogation strategies</i>

1501
01:07:58,667 --> 01:08:01,667
<i>and teach you
how to resist.</i>

1502
01:08:01,751 --> 01:08:04,417
It's a phenomenally
well-designed,

1503
01:08:04,500 --> 01:08:06,667
systematic,
professional program

1504
01:08:06,751 --> 01:08:08,959
from, from beginning to end.

1505
01:08:09,042 --> 01:08:12,292
<i>And it was Jim Mitchell
who helped develop
that program.</i>

1506
01:08:12,375 --> 01:08:15,834
<i>He was actually known for being
a stickler for safety,</i>

1507
01:08:15,918 --> 01:08:17,667
<i>because when they're performing
as interrogators,</i>

1508
01:08:17,751 --> 01:08:20,250
<i>they were simulating torture.</i>

1509
01:08:20,334 --> 01:08:23,209
<i>What we tried
to teach people is
how to be resilient</i>

1510
01:08:23,292 --> 01:08:26,000
in the face of stress,
of coercion, even torture,

1511
01:08:26,083 --> 01:08:30,042
so that you will not
create propaganda.

1512
01:08:30,125 --> 01:08:31,626
Gaudin:
<i>I went to SERE School.</i>

1513
01:08:31,709 --> 01:08:34,209
<i>SERE School
is teaching people,</i>

1514
01:08:34,292 --> 01:08:36,542
<i>if you get captured,
how to stay alive.</i>

1515
01:08:36,626 --> 01:08:39,083
It's teaching people
how to resist.

1516
01:08:39,167 --> 01:08:42,250
It's not eliciting information
from people.

1517
01:08:42,334 --> 01:08:45,542
Jones:<i> These techniques</i>
<i>were used in a coercive way</i>

1518
01:08:45,626 --> 01:08:47,959
to get someone to admit
to something they didn't do,

1519
01:08:48,042 --> 01:08:49,417
to get them
to say anything.

1520
01:08:49,500 --> 01:08:51,125
It was never devised

1521
01:08:51,209 --> 01:08:52,834
even by the worst regimes,

1522
01:08:52,918 --> 01:08:55,250
as a means to obtain
accurate intelligence.

1523
01:08:55,334 --> 01:08:57,292
<i>And that was
Jim's experience.</i>

1524
01:08:57,375 --> 01:08:59,876
<i>He was observing
our US service members</i>

1525
01:08:59,959 --> 01:09:02,083
<i>being exposed to some
of these techniques</i>

1526
01:09:02,167 --> 01:09:03,667
<i>during training.</i>

1527
01:09:03,751 --> 01:09:05,500
Gibney:<i> So the purpose</i>
<i>of the school is not</i>

1528
01:09:05,584 --> 01:09:07,125
<i>to teach interrogation.</i>

1529
01:09:07,209 --> 01:09:08,918
It was to teach people
how to resist interrogation.

1530
01:09:09,000 --> 01:09:11,042
-Is that right?
-Yeah, that's the purpose
of the...

1531
01:09:11,125 --> 01:09:12,959
That's the purpose
of the survival school,

1532
01:09:13,042 --> 01:09:14,834
is to teach people
how to resist interrogation.

1533
01:09:14,918 --> 01:09:17,417
But you know what, if you don't
understand interrogation,

1534
01:09:17,500 --> 01:09:19,500
you're not going to do
a very good job resisting it.

1535
01:09:19,584 --> 01:09:22,000
It isn't gonna happen.

1536
01:09:22,083 --> 01:09:24,667
Gibney:
<i>The kind of interrogation</i>
<i>Mitchell was interested in</i>

1537
01:09:24,751 --> 01:09:27,500
<i>was rooted in another
psychological experiment</i>

1538
01:09:27,584 --> 01:09:30,667
<i>in which dogs were jolted
with electric shocks.</i>

1539
01:09:30,751 --> 01:09:31,959
(dog whimpering)

1540
01:09:32,042 --> 01:09:33,918
<i>The idea was to create,
in animals,</i>

1541
01:09:34,000 --> 01:09:37,209
<i>a feeling called
"learned helplessness."</i>

1542
01:09:37,292 --> 01:09:39,500
<i>To get humans
into that state,</i>

1543
01:09:39,584 --> 01:09:41,417
<i>interrogators would
subject prisoners</i>

1544
01:09:41,500 --> 01:09:44,250
<i>to SERE techniques
until they were helpless</i>

1545
01:09:44,334 --> 01:09:46,417
<i>and would do
or say anything.</i>

1546
01:09:48,125 --> 01:09:51,667
Lawyer: Why did you think
Dr. Mitchell was qualified?

1547
01:09:51,751 --> 01:09:53,918
Because of his experience
with SERE

1548
01:09:54,000 --> 01:09:56,292
and because we needed
to do something different

1549
01:09:56,375 --> 01:09:57,709
than what had been
done before,

1550
01:09:57,792 --> 01:09:59,959
and he looked like
the right person to do it.

1551
01:10:00,042 --> 01:10:01,792
Lawyer: Why did he look like
the right person to do it?

1552
01:10:01,876 --> 01:10:04,334
Because he had
a tremendous expertise

1553
01:10:04,417 --> 01:10:06,542
and, uh...

1554
01:10:06,626 --> 01:10:09,876
he, uh, had
a good vision

1555
01:10:09,959 --> 01:10:11,709
for what needed
to be done.

